ack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[3942,1420],"id":"de0a378e-3534-47df-8cc2-e8d144f2a651","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf08493-task`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Keep Valid Tasks","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"5dacc62e-9166-137e-f87b-dfa642c636ef","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Keep Valid Tasks\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Route by Work Type","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"bc11d618-78a0-43dd-6879-fad31b1e25de","name":"Note: Keep Valid Tasks"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Route by Work Type\n\nRoutes each item to one of 3 lanes: employee, contractor + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Process 'employee' → Google Sheets · ②→ Fast-Track 'contractor' + Alert · ③→ Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"a5cc4d87-fb58-6149-603a-db42603bff8e","name":"Note: Route by Work Type"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Process 'employee' → Google Sheets\n\ngoogleSheets — `appendOrUpdate` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,250],"id":"cf107d52-6506-7173-6109-6210aa9ef5ad","name":"Note: Process 'employee' → Google Sheets"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fast-Track 'contractor' + Alert\n\nmicrosoftOutlook — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,760],"id":"af4f6e5a-47ce-9963-fca1-7b3eff563b9b","name":"Note: Fast-Track 'contractor' + Alert"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,1270],"id":"6b7f1a1c-4b39-ccb2-9865-5fe19f12a839","name":"Note: Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Routed Work\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,520],"id":"19a3d77e-5db9-8645-7b29-bf9452c970ec","name":"Note: Merge Routed Work"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 50 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,520],"id":"86a9aca8-3ff1-57f8-8649-3ead0bc3d10a","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,520],"id":"a5ca4c92-b1bf-8a7e-04e7-3ccd4ed36b1b","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty title","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"236a6dd5-2a69-a80a-6b46-8dd8378c5afa","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty title\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Send Summary to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"d51dc985-8561-3af1-15c9-eea70ad1dd7f","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty title"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"4974f6e6-df20-b3f9-366b-ef0222fd2bd3","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,1540],"id":"d4766f25-0400-de07-1301-cab8e0c7a309","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,1540],"id":"423e6659-d049-0366-6907-393c84b20a63","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Welcome new hires with Asana and Outlook without manual work\n\n**Pattern:** Onboarding Sequence · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nWelcome new hires with Asana and Outlook without manual work. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual onboarding is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Keep Valid Tasks → Route by Work Type → Process 'employee' → Google Sheets → Merge Routed Work → Cap Batch Volume → Align Field Names → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to onboarding sequence without manual effort\n- Anyone automating onboarding in software development\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Improves response time\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"edee132d-b054-f3a6-9b0b-32c59e26a8ec","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"94d7ad55-0046-85a6-c6b2-9b7bc01a6db7","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"989a2477-4b4e-8655-5d66-e3d1c437a569","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your onboarding process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"ef7521e9-ee9c-b384-d152-5f0b080482d9","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Keep Valid Tasks","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Keep Valid Tasks":{"main":[[{"node":"Route by Work Type","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Route by Work Type":{"main":[[{"node":"Process 'employee' → Google Sheets","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Fast-Track 'contractor' + Alert","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Process 'employee' → Google Sheets":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fast-Track 'contractor' + Alert":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Merge Routed Work":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty title","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty title":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"93679665-bf35-4e2d-856f-6cf326fb0c67","id":"FDX08493"}